{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1283,"text":"The FBI is responsible\nfor more terrorism plots"},{"time":3504,"text":"in the United States"},{"time":5175,"text":"than any other organization."},{"time":7771,"text":"More than al Qaeda,"},{"time":9625,"text":"more than al Shabaab,"},{"time":11010,"text":"more than the Islamic State,"},{"time":12560,"text":"more than all of them combined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15354,"text":"This isn't likely how you\nthink about the FBI."},{"time":18011,"text":"You probably think of FBI agents\ngunning down bad guys like John Dillinger,"},{"time":22066,"text":"or arresting corrupt politicians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25207,"text":"After the 9/11 terrorist attacks,"},{"time":26858,"text":"the FBI became less concerned \n"},{"time":28331,"text":"with gangsters and \ncrooked elected officials."},{"time":30940,"text":"The new target became terrorists,"},{"time":33402,"text":"and the pursuit of terrorists \nhas consumed the FBI."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36823,"text":"Every year, the Bureau spends\n3.3 billion dollars"},{"time":39618,"text":"on domestic counterterrorism activities."},{"time":42222,"text":"Compare than to just 2.6 billion dollars\ncombined for organized crime,"},{"time":45823,"text":"financial fraud, public corruption\n"},{"time":47999,"text":"and all other types of traditional\ncriminal activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50777,"text":"I've spent years pouring through\nthe case files"},{"time":52973,"text":"of terrorism prosecutions in \nthe United States,"},{"time":55805,"text":"and I've come to \nthe conclusion that the FBI"},{"time":58074,"text":"is much better at creating terrorists\nthan it is at catching terrorists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63083,"text":"In the 14 years since 9/11,"},{"time":65097,"text":"you can count about six real \nterrorist attacks in the United States."},{"time":68681,"text":"These include the Boston Marathon \nbombings in 2013,"},{"time":71751,"text":"as well as failed attacks,"},{"time":73040,"text":"such as the time when \na man named Faisal Shahzad"},{"time":75505,"text":"tried to deliver a car bomb\nto Times Square."},{"time":78507,"text":"In those same 14 years,"},{"time":80122,"text":"the Bureau, however, has bragged"},{"time":81754,"text":"about how it's foiled dozens\nof terrorism plots."},{"time":84945,"text":"In all, the FBI has arrested\nmore than 175 people"},{"time":89183,"text":"in aggressive, undercover \nconterterrorism stings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92629,"text":"These operations, which are usually\nled by an informant,"},{"time":95467,"text":"provide the means and opportunity,"},{"time":97293,"text":"and sometimes even the idea,"},{"time":99225,"text":"for mentally ill and \neconomically desperate people"},{"time":102081,"text":"to become what we now term terrorists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106061,"text":"After 9/11, the FBI was given an edict:"},{"time":108368,"text":"never again."},{"time":109586,"text":"Never another attack on American soil."},{"time":112707,"text":"FBI agents were told to find terrorists\nbefore they struck."},{"time":115667,"text":"To do this, agents recruited a network\nof more than 15,000 informants nationwide,"},{"time":120507,"text":"all looking for anyone who \nmight be dangerous."},{"time":123276,"text":"An informant can earn \n100,000 dollars or more"},{"time":125647,"text":"for every terrorism case \nthey bring to the FBI."},{"time":128752,"text":"That's right, the FBI is paying\nmostly criminals and con men"},{"time":132025,"text":"six figures to spy on communities\nin the United States,"},{"time":134926,"text":"but mostly Muslim American communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138103,"text":"These informants nab people like \nAbu Khalid Abdul-Latif"},{"time":141277,"text":"and Walli Mujahidh."},{"time":143148,"text":"Both are mentally ill."},{"time":144653,"text":"Abdul-Latif had a history of huffing\ngasoline and attempting suicide."},{"time":148016,"text":"Mujahidh had schizoaffective disorder,"},{"time":150537,"text":"he had trouble distinguishing between\nreality and fantasy."},{"time":153745,"text":"In 2012, the FBI arrested these two men"},{"time":156227,"text":"for conspiring to attack a military\nrecruiting station outside Seattle"},{"time":160039,"text":"with weapons provided, \nof course, by the FBI."},{"time":164363,"text":"The FBI's informant was Robert Childs,"},{"time":167068,"text":"a convicted rapist and child molester"},{"time":169027,"text":"who was paid 90,000 dollars \nfor his work on the case."},{"time":172361,"text":"This isn't an outlier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173849,"text":"In 2009, an FBI informant\nwho had fled Pakistan on murder charges"},{"time":177671,"text":"led four men in a plot to bomb \nsynagogues in the Bronx."},{"time":181575,"text":"The lead defendant was James Cromitie,"},{"time":183526,"text":"a broke Walmart employee\nwith a history of mental problems."},{"time":186476,"text":"And the informant had offered \nhim 250,000 dollars"},{"time":189201,"text":"if he participated in that plot."},{"time":191587,"text":"There are many more examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194232,"text":"Today, The Intercept\npublished my new story"},{"time":196350,"text":"about a counterterrorism sting in Tampa\ninvolving Sami Osmakac,"},{"time":200065,"text":"a young man who was living \nnear Tampa, Florida."},{"time":203218,"text":"Osmakac also had \nschizoaffective disorder."},{"time":205890,"text":"He too was broke,"},{"time":206895,"text":"and he had no connections to \ninternational terrorist groups."},{"time":209932,"text":"Nonetheless,"},{"time":210773,"text":"an FBI informant gave him a job,\nhanded him money,"},{"time":214617,"text":"introduced him to an undercover agent\nposing as a terrorist,"},{"time":217438,"text":"and lured him in a plot\nto bomb an Irish bar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220727,"text":"But here's what's interesting:"},{"time":222684,"text":"The lead undercover agent --"},{"time":224138,"text":"you can see him in this picture\nwith his face blurred --"},{"time":226776,"text":"would go back to the Tampa field office\nwith his recording equipment on."},{"time":230287,"text":"Behind closed doors,"},{"time":231608,"text":"FBI agents admitted that what\nthey were doing was farcical."},{"time":234987,"text":"A federal judge doesn't want you\nto hear about these conversations."},{"time":238216,"text":"He sealed the transcripts and placed\nthem under a protective order"},{"time":241367,"text":"in an attempt to prevent someone like me\nfrom doing something like this."},{"time":245574,"text":"Behind closed doors, the lead agent,"},{"time":247585,"text":"the squad supervisor,"},{"time":248916,"text":"described their would-be terrorist"},{"time":250551,"text":"as a \"retarded fool who didn't have\na pot to piss in.\""},{"time":253182,"text":"They described his terrorist ambitions\n"},{"time":255009,"text":"as wishy-washy and\na pipe dream scenario."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258998,"text":"But that didn't stop the FBI."},{"time":260756,"text":"They provided Sami Osmakac \neverything he needed."},{"time":264092,"text":"They gave him a car bomb,\nthey gave him an AK-47,"},{"time":267804,"text":"they helped him make a so-called\nmartyrdom video,"},{"time":270386,"text":"and they even gave \nhim money for a taxi cab"},{"time":272480,"text":"so that he could get to where\nthey wanted him to go."},{"time":276004,"text":"As they were working the sting,"},{"time":277814,"text":"the squad supervisor tells his agents\nhe wanted a Hollywood ending."},{"time":282527,"text":"And he got a Hollywood ending."},{"time":285048,"text":"When Sami Osmakac attempted\nto deliver what he thought"},{"time":287609,"text":"was a car bomb,"},{"time":288905,"text":"he was arrested, convicted and \nsentenced to 40 years in prison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293604,"text":"Sami Osmakac isn't alone."},{"time":296223,"text":"He's one of more than \n175 so-called terrorists,"},{"time":298825,"text":"for whom the FBI has created \nHollywood endings."},{"time":303813,"text":"U.S. government officials call this\nthe War on Terror."},{"time":306982,"text":"It's really just theater,"},{"time":308759,"text":"a national security theater,"},{"time":311089,"text":"with mentally ill men like Sami Osmakac"},{"time":313574,"text":"unwitting actors in a \ncarefully choreographed production"},{"time":316621,"text":"brought to you by the FBI."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318829,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319956,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329090,"text":"Tom Rielly: So, those are some\npretty strong accusations,"},{"time":332421,"text":"pretty strong charges."},{"time":335098,"text":"How can you back this up?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":336711,"text":"Trevor Aaronson: My research began in 2010"},{"time":338727,"text":"when I received a grant from the \nInvestigative Reporting Program"},{"time":341795,"text":"at U.C. Berkeley,"},{"time":342730,"text":"and a research assistant and I"},{"time":344162,"text":"put together a database\nof all terrorism prosecutions"},{"time":346635,"text":"at the time during \nthe first decade after 9/11."},{"time":349651,"text":"And we used the court file\nto find out whether"},{"time":352458,"text":"the defendants had any connections\nto international terrorist groups,"},{"time":355881,"text":"whether an informant was used,"},{"time":357364,"text":"and whether the informant\nplayed the role of an agent provocateur"},{"time":360506,"text":"by providing the means and opportunity."},{"time":362373,"text":"And we submitted that to the FBI"},{"time":363950,"text":"and we asked them to respond\nto our database."},{"time":366064,"text":"If they believed there were any errors,"},{"time":368021,"text":"we asked them to tell us what they were\nand we'd go back and check"},{"time":371154,"text":"and they never challenged any\nof our findings."},{"time":373382,"text":"Later, I used that data \nin a magazine article"},{"time":375580,"text":"and later in my book,"},{"time":376629,"text":"and on appearances on places\nlike CBS and NPR,"},{"time":379176,"text":"they were offered that opportunity again"},{"time":381083,"text":"to say, \"Trevor Aaronson's \nfindings are wrong.\""},{"time":383333,"text":"And they've never\ncome forward and said,"},{"time":385193,"text":"\"These are the problems\nwith those findings.\""},{"time":387314,"text":"So the data has since been used \nby groups like Human Rights Watch"},{"time":390455,"text":"on its recent report on \nthese types of sting operations."},{"time":393157,"text":"And so far, the FBI has never \nreally responded"},{"time":395796,"text":"to these charges that it's really\nnot catching terrorists"},{"time":399022,"text":"so much as it's catching\nmentally ill people"},{"time":401167,"text":"that it can dress up as terrorists \nin these types of sting operations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405849,"text":"TR: So The Intercept is that new\ninvestigative journalism website,"},{"time":409327,"text":"that's cofounded by Glenn Greenwald."},{"time":411095,"text":"Tell us about your article \nand why there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414674,"text":"TA: The Intercept seemed to be\nthe most logical place for this"},{"time":417654,"text":"because my article is \nreally leveraging the fact that"},{"time":420723,"text":"a source had leaked to me\ntranscripts of these"},{"time":423208,"text":"private FBI conversations\nthat a federal judge had sealed"},{"time":426155,"text":"based on the government's claim \nthat their release"},{"time":428556,"text":"would irreparably damage \nthe U.S. government's"},{"time":430748,"text":"law enforcement strategy."},{"time":432852,"text":"So a place like The Intercept\nwas set up to protect journalists"},{"time":435831,"text":"and publish their work"},{"time":436890,"text":"when they're dealing with \nvery sensitive matters like this."},{"time":439719,"text":"So my story in The Intercept, \nwhich was just published today,"},{"time":442618,"text":"tells the story of how Sami Osmakac\nwas set up in this FBI sting"},{"time":445953,"text":"and goes into much greater detail."},{"time":447633,"text":"In this talk, I could only\nhighlight the things that they said,"},{"time":450597,"text":"such as calling him a \"retarded fool.\""},{"time":452434,"text":"But it was much more elaborate,"},{"time":453916,"text":"they went to great lengths\nto put money in Sami Osmakac's hands,"},{"time":457012,"text":"which he then used to purchase weapons\nfrom the undercover agent."},{"time":460068,"text":"When he went to trial,"},{"time":461208,"text":"the central piece of evidence \nwas that he paid for these weapons,"},{"time":464339,"text":"when in truth, these transcripts show\nhow the FBI orchestrated"},{"time":467260,"text":"someone who was essentially\nmentally ill and broke"},{"time":469660,"text":"to get money to then \npay for weapons"},{"time":471879,"text":"that they could then charge him\nin a conspiracy for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474387,"text":"TR: One final question."},{"time":476514,"text":"Less than 10 days ago,"},{"time":478035,"text":"the FBI arrested some potential \nISIS suspects in Brooklyn,"},{"time":481187,"text":"saying that they might\nbe headed to Syria,"},{"time":484725,"text":"and were those real,\nor examples of more of the same?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":487622,"text":"TA: Well so far, we only know\nwhat's come out in the court file,"},{"time":490636,"text":"but they seem to suggest it's another\nexample of the same."},{"time":493641,"text":"These types of sting operations \nhave moved from flavor to flavor."},{"time":496823,"text":"So initially it was al Qaeda plots,"},{"time":498991,"text":"and now the Islamic State\nis the current flavor."},{"time":501305,"text":"What's worth noting about that case\nis that the three men that were charged"},{"time":504874,"text":"only began the plot to go to Syria"},{"time":506724,"text":"after the introduction\nof the FBI informant,"},{"time":508801,"text":"and in fact, the FBI informant had helped\nthem with the travel documents"},{"time":512251,"text":"that they needed."},{"time":513167,"text":"In kind of a comical turn \nin that particular case,"},{"time":515784,"text":"one of the defendant's mother\nhad found out"},{"time":517850,"text":"that he was interested in going to Syria\nand had hid his passport."},{"time":521016,"text":"So it's unclear that even if he had\nshowed up at the airport,"},{"time":523949,"text":"that he ever could have gone anywhere."},{"time":525777,"text":"So yes, there are people who might\nbe interested in joining the Islamic State"},{"time":529420,"text":"in the United States,"},{"time":530428,"text":"and those are people that the United \nStates government should be looking at"},{"time":534050,"text":"to see if they're interested\nin violence here."},{"time":536329,"text":"In this particular case, given\nthe evidence that's so far come out,"},{"time":539509,"text":"it suggests the FBI made\nit possible for these guys"},{"time":541904,"text":"to move along in a plan to go to Syria"},{"time":543984,"text":"when they were never close \nto that in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546592,"text":"TR: Thanks a lot, that's amazing.\nTA: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548825,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}